-- Hungarian Lawmakers Pass Amended 2012 Budget, MTI Reports
-- B y   E d i t h   B a l a z s
-- 2011-12-20T06:38:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-20/hungarian-lawmakers-pass-amended-2012-budget-mti-reports.html
Hungary’s ruling coalition lawmakers
passed the 2012 budget this morning after changing the draft’s
cornerstone numbers hours before the vote, state news service
 MTI  reported.  The government is targeting a budget  deficit  of 2.5 percent
of gross domestic product next year and reckons with economic
growth of 0.5 percent and average inflation of 4.2 percent, MTI
said. The average exchange rate in the budget is 299.4 forint
per euro, MTI reported.  All three opposition parties voted against the draft,
according to the news service.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Edith Balazs in Budapest at 
 ebalazs1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
